==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Houseleek
<hw>House"leek`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>House</ets>
+ <ets>leek</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A succulent plant of
the genus <gen>Sempervivum</gen> (<spn>Sempervivum tectorum</spn>),
originally a native of subalpine Europe, but now found very generally on
old walls and roofs. It is very tenacious of life under drought and
heat; -- called also <altname>ayegreen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Houseless</ent>⟦br⟧
